<Layout
    title="About Calculemus"
    description="The student-run AI team at Leiden University (LIACS)."
    pubDate={new Date('May 08 2026')}
>
    <p>
        <strong>"Calculemus"</strong> means <em>Let us calculate</em>. It's a phrase from Leibniz, who wanted to solve problems purely through computation. We're a team of computer science and AI students at <strong>Leiden University (LIACS)</strong> trying to do exactly that with modern ML.
    </p>

    <h3>What we do</h3>
    <p>
        We focus on the mechanics of artificial intelligence, by participating in research driven challenges. We care about understanding architectures, optimizing them, and building systems that actually work in the real world.
    </p>

    <h3>The Community</h3>
    <p>
        Studying AI is easier (and a lot more fun) when you aren't doing it alone. Calculemus acts as a hub for students who want to build, debug, and research together. We run a few main events throughout the year:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Tech Talks:</strong> Technical deep dives by LIACS researchers and industry engineers.</li>
        <li><strong>Hackathons:</strong> 24-hour sprints to build working models from scratch.</li>
        <li><strong>Coding Nights:</strong> Low-key evenings where we bring laptops, grab pizza, and write code together.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Join us</h3>
    <p>
        Whether you're a master's student training models for your thesis or a first-year who just wrote their first PyTorch training loop, you're welcome here. Check out our <a href="/events">Events</a> page to see when we're meeting next.
    </p>
</Layout>